{"lemma":"غارَةُ","slug":"غارَةُ","root":"غ.#.ر","root_slug":"غ-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-_-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n32613"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%BA%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"raid, encroachment","examples":[{"text":"لقي 38 من ميليشيات الحوثي مصرعهم في سلسلة غارات للتحالف العربي استهدفت اجتماعا ومواقع عسكرية في (دمت)، شمالي محافظة الضالع اليمنية.","english":"Thirty-eight Houthi militias met their death in a series of raids by the Arab alliance targeting a meeting and military sites in Dumit, in the north of the Yemeni governorate of Ḍaliʿ."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"singulative of غَار (ḡār, “bay laurel”)","tags":["form-of","singulative"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ɣaː.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32613","headword_ar":"غَارَةٌ","root":"gwr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agaAra","text_ar":"اَغَارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A going away into a country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A quick running,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehement running,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) of a horse, (Mgh, Msb, TA,) and of a fox; (Mgh;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gawiyrN","text_ar":"غَوِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", of a fox. (TA.) ―         -b3-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A raid;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an incursion into the territory of an enemy; or a sudden,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an unexpected, attack upon an enemy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the territories"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dwellings of an enemy, with a party of armed horsemen, and engagement with them in conflict; an urging of horses upon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against, a people;"},{"kind":"text","text":"generally,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hostile,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"predatory, incursion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making such an incursion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] a subst. [or quasi-inf. n.] from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agaAra EalaY","text_ar":"اَغَارَ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaduw~i","text_ar":"العَدُوِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Plunder,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pillage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  And hence, (Mgh, Msb,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Horsemen making a raid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sudden,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an unexpected, attack, upon an enemy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the dwellings of an enemy, and engaging with them in conflict: horsemen urging their horses upon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against, a people:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayolN mugiyrapN","text_ar":"خَيْلٌ مُغِيرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Mgh, Msb, TA:) and one says also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xyl migiyrapN","text_ar":"خيل مِغِيرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr. (TA.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$an~a Ealayohimu AlgaArapa","text_ar":"شَنَّ عَلَيْهِمُ الغَارَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He scattered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$n","text_ar":"شن"},{"kind":"text","text":", and Mgh * and Msb, *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$n","text_ar":"شن"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon them"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the horsemen making a raid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sudden attack, and engaging in conflict,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the horsemen urging their horses"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, K.) The poet (El-Kumeyt Ibn-Maaroof, TA) says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wanaHonu SabaHonaA A=la najoraAna gaArapF\n                      \n                     \n                        tamiyma bona mur~K waAlr~imaAHa Aln~awaAdisaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And we gave as a morning-drink to"},{"kind":"text","text":"the people of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Nejrán a troop of horsemen making a raid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sudden attack, upon them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"urging their horses against them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely the tribe of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Temeem Ibn-Murr, and the piercing spears"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: he means,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqayonaAhumo","text_ar":"سَقَيْنَاهُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayolFA mugiyrapF","text_ar":"خَيْلًا مُغِيرَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tmym bn mr~","text_ar":"تميم بن مرّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put in the accus. case as a substitute for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gArp","text_ar":"غارة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabolN","text_ar":"حَبْلٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$adiydu AlgaArapi","text_ar":"شَدِيدُ الغَارَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A rope twisted hard;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard in respect of the twisting;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaArapN","text_ar":"غَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being in this case [as in that first mentioned above] a subst. standing in stead of the inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_igaArap","text_ar":"اـِغَارَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabolN mugaArN","text_ar":"حَبْلٌ مُغَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, TA;) applied to a rope that is twisted with another. (TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misoHalN","text_ar":"مِسْحَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlgaArapu","text_ar":"الغَارَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The navel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, K:) app. so called because of its depth. (Sgh, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","Msb","TA","S","Sgh","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}